Qtag is a cross-platform Qt-based application for editing audio tags.
Supports ID3v1, ID3v2, Xiph Comments and various other tag formats.
Includes some advanced options like multiple tagging, copying tags, tagging from path/filename...
It is licensed under the Mozzila Public License v2.0. ( https://www.mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/index.txt )


**Linux:**

Pick a package suitable for your system here: https://github.com/amethystAnt/Qtag/releases

If you want to compile it, install Qt 5 and TagLib (and obviously GCC and Git) and open a command line:

  $git clone http://www.github.com/amethystAnt/Qtag.git
  $git checkout stable
  $cd Qtag/src
  $qmake-qt5 # or just qmake could also work
  $make
  #make install


**Windows:**

Download an installer here: https://github.com/amethystAnt/Qtag-installer/releases/


**Others:**

If you'd like to compile it on *BSD or OS X, do it on your own.
